Description: Fragment of a dark stone statue naming Hori; columns of Hieroglyphic text on three sides.
Curator's comments: Possibly part of statue of "Hori IX", cf. SAK 22: 187ff (Jansen-Winkeln)

Publication of texts: Karl Jansen-Winkeln, Inschriften der Spätzeit. Teil II: Die 22.-24. Dynastie, Wiesbaden 2007, p. 218 (23.22). Publication with photos and drawings: Helmut Brandl, Untersuchungen zur Privatplastik der Dritten Zwischenzeit: Typologie - Ikonographie - Stilistik, Berlin 2008, p. 217, pl. 121.
Acquisition name: Purchased from: Rev Greville John Chester
